      • addEntry

        public java.lang.Integer addEntry(java.lang.String entry,
                         java.lang.String contentType,
                         java.lang.String patientID,
                         java.lang.String studyUID,
                         java.lang.String objectUID)
                           throws java.lang.Exception
        Add an entry to the log.
        Parameters:
        entry - the entry to be made in the audit log.
        contentType - the contentType of the entry (not used by the audit log itself, but may be used by applications that parse audit log entries). If the contentType parameter is null, no entry is made in the contentType table.
        patientID - the key in the patientID index under which the entry is to listed, or null if no entry is to be made in the patientID index.
        studyUID - the key in the studyUID index under which the entry is to listed, or null if no entry is to be made in the studyUID index.
        objectUID - the key in the objectUID index under which the entry is to listed, or null if no entry is to be made in the objectUID index.
        Returns:
        the entry ID of the audit log entry.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if the entry could not be made in the audit log.

      • addEntryReference

        public java.lang.Integer addEntryReference(java.lang.Integer entryID,
                                  java.lang.String patientID,
                                  java.lang.String studyUID,
                                  java.lang.String objectUID)
                                    throws java.lang.Exception
        Add index entries for an object already stored.
        Parameters:
        entryID - the ID of the existing entry to be referenced in the audit log.
        patientID - the key in the patientID index under which the entry is to listed, or null if no entry is to be made in the patientID index.
        studyUID - the key in the studyUID index under which the entry is to listed, or null if no entry is to be made in the studyUID index.
        objectUID - the key in the objectUID index under which the entry is to listed, or null if no entry is to be made in the objectUID index.
        Returns:
        the entry ID of the audit log entry.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if the entry could not be made in the audit log.
